    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with a clear focus on aggressive base-running and high-floor match-ups. Our primary offensive catalysts are **Mickey Moniak** (73.38) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (72.92), who both benefit from superior park factors and optimal spots in the order. **Mickey Moniak** is the standout play; while he faces a difficult catcher-pitcher battery against Brazob\u00e1n, his top-of-the-order positioning and dynamic platoon advantage make him our highest-projected asset. Similarly, **Seiya Suzuki** (72.32) earns a strong start thanks to an inviting 6.57 xERA matchup against Petty and favorable wind conditions that inflate his projection by 5%.\n\nThe most difficult personnel decision today involved **Cole Young**, whose 46.11 efficiency score fell just short of the threshold required to displace **Kyle Karros** (45.40). While **Kyle Karros** suffers from a significant park-related dip and a poor matchup against Brazob\u00e1n\u2019s elite 1.87s exchange time, his raw volume and versatility keep him in the lineup over **Cole Young**. Meanwhile, **Austin Riley** remains on the bench (42.29) as he struggles to navigate a difficult matchup against Gilbert, and **Alex Freeland** is sidelined entirely as his 39.44 score dips below our strict \"Zebras\" floor of 40.0, necessitating a cap-preservation strategy.\n\nWe are carefully monitoring the risks associated with our stolen base specialists. **Jose Caballero** (50.33) is a start despite his bottom-of-the-order assignment, as his speed profile remains vital for our scarcity-driven strategy; however, he faces a daunting matchup against Baz. The primary warning for the day is the defensive efficiency of the opposition; both **Kyle Karros** and **Mickey Moniak** must contend with an elite hold pitcher in the Brazob\u00e1n matchup, which could dampen the impact of their speed. We are resting **Corbin Carroll** today due to the team\u2019s schedule, keeping him fresh for the upcoming series.",
